M||tx|---
M|Prin|tx|Understand behavior by examining the whole sy, not isolated parts. sy behavior emerges from the interactions btw cp, not from the cp themselves.
M|Core|tx|\| Concept \| Definition \| Example \|
M|Core|tx|\|---------\|-----------\|---------\|
M|Core|tx|\| Feedback loops \| Output feeds back as input, amplifying or dampening \| Team velocity drops, so management adds process, which drops velocity further \|
M|Core|tx|\| Emergence \| sy behavior not predictable from individual parts \| Microservices that each work fine but cr cascading failures together \|
M|Core|tx|\| Delays \| Effects lag behind causes \| tc debt accrues silently, then explodes during a ct feature push \|
M|Core|tx|\| Leverage points \| Small changes w/ outsized impact \| Fixing a shared library bug vs patching each consumer \|
M|Core|tx|\| Mental md \| Assumptions that shape how we interpret the sy \| "More engineers = faster delivery" (ignoring Brooks's Law) \|
M|Deci|tx|Use this md during **Challenge** (Steps 5-6) to identify second-order effects and feedback loops.
M|Veri|When|
M|Veri|tx|1. What feedback loops does this decision cr or break?
M|Veri|tx|2. What are the second-order effects? Third-order?
M|Veri|tx|3. Where are the delays btw action and consequence?
M|Veri|tx|4. What leverage points exist? Are we acting on them or on symptoms?
M|Veri|tx|5. What mental md are we assuming that might be wrong?
M|Red |tx|\| Signal \| Risk \|
M|Red |tx|\|--------\|------\|
M|Red |tx|\| "This only affects cp X" \| Ignoring sy interconnections \|
M|Red |tx|\| "We'll see results immediately" \| Ignoring delays in the sy \|
M|Red |tx|\| "More resources will fix it" \| Linear thinking in a nonlinear sy \|
M|Red |tx|\| "We fixed the symptom" \| Root cause unaddressed, will resurface \|
M|Red || Op|metric becomes the target, not the goal \|
M|Seco|For |
M|Seco|tx|```
M|Seco|Deci|[proposed action]
M|Seco|-> F|[immediate, intended effect]
M|Seco|-> S|[downstream consequence]
M|Seco|-> T|[further ripple effect]
M|Seco|tx|```
M|Cont|it|"What if this fix creates a worse problem elsewhere in the sy?"
M|Cont|it|"What feedback loop are we accidentally creating?"
M|Cont|it|"Are we treating the symptom or the cause?"
M|Cont|it|"What will this look like in 6 months when delays manifest?"
M|Fail|it|Fixing a symptom while the root cause generates new symptoms
M|Fail|it|Creating reinforcing feedback loops that accelerate problems
M|Fail|it|Ignoring delays and declaring sc before consequences arrive
M|Fail|it|Optimizing a subsystem at the expense of the whole sy
M|Fail|it|Missing leverage points and applying effort where impact is lowest
M|Prac|Befo|
M|Prac|it|[ ] sy boundaries defined (what is inside/outside scope)
M|Prac|it|[ ] Feedback loops identified (reinforcing and balancing)
M|Prac|it|[ ] Second-order effects traced for at least 2 levels
M|Prac|it|[ ] Delays btw action and effect estimated
M|Prac|it|[ ] Leverage points identified and targeted
M|Prac|it|[ ] Mental md assumptions stated explicitly
M|Rela|- Ga|complex systems evolve from simple ones
M|Rela|- Ch|understand the sy before changing it
M|Rela|- Su|examine the full sy, not just visible outputs